<subSubSection id="C3216524FFDCFFA1FF43FD97FAE5FD41" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8436AFFFDCFFA1FF43FD97FAE5FD41" blockId="5.[136,1452,518,689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">
The original material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FE6EFD96FDE4FDD1" authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1828" box="[421,559,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FE6EFD96FDE4FDD1" box="[421,559,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is preserved in P where Saint-Hilaire worked (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FB99FD97FA94FDD1" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[1106,1375,518,544]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 1064). It is represented by two duplicates, neither of which is mentioned in the protologue. Therefore, according to Art. 9.3 of the ICN, we designate herein specimen P 
<date id="FF85106FFFDCFFA1FD12FDDFFC81FD99" box="[729,842,590,616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" value="2940-02-14">02142940</date>
as the 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFDCFFA1FC50FDDFFBC9FD99" box="[923,1026,590,616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FBE2FDDEFB79FD99" authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1828" box="[1065,1202,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FBE2FDDEFB79FD99" box="[1065,1202,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by choosing the most complete specimen and one that best represents the protologue’s description. Based on 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FB4DFDE3FA9FFD7C" author="Schumann, K." box="[1158,1364,626,653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FAAFFDE2FF18FD40" author="Burret, K. E. M." pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="592 - 880" refId="ref7098" refString="Burret, K. E. M. (1926) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Tiliaceen. Notizblatt des Botanischen Gartens und Museums zu Berlin-Dahlem 9 (88): 592 - 880. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3994327" type="journal article" year="1926">Burret (1926)</bibRefCitation>
and the present study, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FCC0FD06FC59FD41" authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1828" box="[779,914,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FCC0FD06FC59FD41" box="[779,914,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as an accepted species.
</paragraph>
